This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an optimization algorithm for improving the performance of a neural network, which is a common topic in machine learning.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on improving the conditioning of an extreme learning machine, which is a type of neural network. Therefore, it is likely to belong to this sub-category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an algorithm for optimizing the performance of a neural network, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an algorithm for improving the performance of a system, which is a common topic in systems and control.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes an algorithm for optimizing the performance of a computational model, which is a common topic in computational engineering and science.
